heaviest_rainfall.status: The most intense rainfall recorded took place on 04 January 2025, with precipitation totalling 36.8mm.  The rain fell at 4.6mm per hour at times over the course of the 37.2 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: There was a torrential downpour today where the rain reached a maximum intensity of 16.2mm per hour (ranked 4th in our records).  The storm lasted 6.9 hours and 9.36mm of precipitation fell during that time.  The rain rate reached 27.0mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

summary.description:
Today, cooler for the feels like temperature (down 2.4°C), outside temperature (down 2.2°C), and inside temperature (down 1.8°C) and more moisture-laden outside humidity (up 8%).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in cloud levels (up 654 m) and light levels (up 5750 lux).

The past week and month had observable variation in cloud levels (up 1251 m), light levels (up 7678 lux), and rainfall (down 0.4 mm) when compared to today.
